1
00:00:10,625 --> 00:00:18,416
[bell ringing]

2
00:00:22,041 --> 00:00:23,208
[SAKURA gasps]

3
00:00:23,291 --> 00:00:24,875
Wait, come back!

4
00:00:28,541 --> 00:00:30,708
[AYANOKOJI] American
Anthropologist Edward Hall

5
00:00:30,791 --> 00:00:35,375
divided the concept of personal
space into four general zones.

6
00:00:35,458 --> 00:00:38,583
He named one of these
the "intimate space" zone.

7
00:00:38,666 --> 00:00:41,416
With the "close phase"
contained therein.

8
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:44,625
The latter is near enough
for someone to hug them.

9
00:00:44,708 --> 00:00:48,500
Many resist letting
others into this zone.

10
00:00:48,583 --> 00:00:50,500
However, some people
seem to enter

11
00:00:50,583 --> 00:00:52,833
into everyone's
close phase easily.

12
00:00:52,916 --> 00:00:54,625
Kushida's one of those.

13
00:00:54,708 --> 00:00:56,666
Even if she enters
someone's close phase,

14
00:00:56,750 --> 00:00:59,208
she manages not to trigger
an aversive reaction.

15
00:00:59,291 --> 00:01:00,458
[SAKURA panting]

16
00:01:00,541 --> 00:01:04,250
[AYANOKOJI] Even so,
Sakura resisted Kushida.

17
00:01:07,583 --> 00:01:12,458
[AYANOKOJI] For some unknown
reason, she ran away from her.

18
00:01:12,541 --> 00:01:15,333
She couldn't even
look her in the eye.

19
00:01:16,791 --> 00:01:18,916
[AYANOKOJI] Why does she fear
contact with others?

20
00:02:49,666 --> 00:02:51,416
Um. I'm so sorry!

21
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:54,041
You two are very kind to agree
to come with me for this.

22
00:02:54,125 --> 00:02:56,375
No, this whole thing
is my fault!

23
00:02:56,458 --> 00:02:58,041
I'm the one who
owes you an apology

24
00:02:58,125 --> 00:02:59,458
for breaking your camera!

25
00:02:59,541 --> 00:03:02,833
[SAKURA] Thanks, but I should
have been more careful.

26
00:03:02,916 --> 00:03:05,000
[AYANOKOJI] So, you're going
to the electronics store

27
00:03:05,083 --> 00:03:07,458
where you got your
camera to get it fixed.

28
00:03:07,541 --> 00:03:09,916
I understand that part.

29
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,333
But why did I have to come?

30
00:03:11,416 --> 00:03:13,208
[KIKYO giggles]

31
00:03:13,291 --> 00:03:15,291
I need you, too.

32
00:03:15,375 --> 00:03:16,791
[SERVICE MAN 5A]
Man, what a bummer.

33
00:03:16,875 --> 00:03:19,625
This is no good.
I see what's wrong here.

34
00:03:19,708 --> 00:03:21,875
Looks like a power
issue if you ask me.

35
00:03:21,958 --> 00:03:23,833
Mm. Definitely.

36
00:03:25,708 --> 00:03:27,583
[SERVICE MAN 5A]
Do you have a warranty with you?

37
00:03:27,666 --> 00:03:28,916
Should be covered.

38
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,291
You did remember to
bring it with you, right?

39
00:03:31,375 --> 00:03:32,791
[SAKURA]
Mm-hm.

40
00:03:34,875 --> 00:03:38,541
[gasps] It hasn't expired, yay!

41
00:03:38,625 --> 00:03:41,541
You could have the broken
part, uh--replaced.

42
00:03:41,625 --> 00:03:42,708
Completely free of charge.

43
00:03:42,791 --> 00:03:44,041
[gasps]

44
00:03:45,625 --> 00:03:48,125
[AYANOKOJI] I see.
Sakura's scared of strangers.

45
00:03:48,208 --> 00:03:50,333
Of course, this guy
would freak her out.

46
00:03:50,416 --> 00:03:53,208
I'm here because she wanted
strength in numbers.

47
00:03:54,458 --> 00:03:56,750
Um. Do you know how
long the repairs will take?

48
00:03:56,833 --> 00:03:58,666
[SERVICE MAN 5A]
Two or three days max, I think.

49
00:03:58,750 --> 00:04:00,250
But don't quote me.

50
00:04:00,333 --> 00:04:03,416
I need you to fill out this
form, but not the whole thing.

51
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:06,041
Fill out your name here,
home address,

52
00:04:06,125 --> 00:04:09,458
and your cell phone number.

53
00:04:09,541 --> 00:04:10,791
[gasps]

54
00:04:16,125 --> 00:04:17,083
Are you all right?

55
00:04:17,166 --> 00:04:20,625
[gasps] Uh, yeah.

56
00:04:23,458 --> 00:04:25,958
[SAKURA whimpering]

57
00:04:28,208 --> 00:04:30,583
[AYANOKOJI]
Let me do it.

58
00:04:30,666 --> 00:04:32,291
When the repairs are complete,

59
00:04:32,375 --> 00:04:34,333
please contact me
instead of Sakura.

60
00:04:34,416 --> 00:04:36,000
[SERVICE MAN 5A]
What?! Hey, wait a minute!

61
00:04:36,083 --> 00:04:38,083
The camera belongs
to her, doesn't it?

62
00:04:38,166 --> 00:04:41,083
I don't think we can do that.

63
00:04:41,166 --> 00:04:43,041
I'm not comfortable with this.

64
00:04:43,125 --> 00:04:44,541
You saw the warranty.

65
00:04:44,625 --> 00:04:46,375
It notes the time and
location of purchase

66
00:04:46,458 --> 00:04:48,458
so you shouldn't need
her information.

67
00:04:48,541 --> 00:04:50,625
I understand that
it's store policy,

68
00:04:50,708 --> 00:04:52,541
but you won't get in trouble.

69
00:04:52,625 --> 00:04:54,875
I can't imagine there
being a legal issue.

70
00:04:54,958 --> 00:04:55,958
You don't have to worry.

71
00:04:56,041 --> 00:04:58,916
Well. Are you sure about that?

72
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,458
[gasping]

73
00:05:01,791 --> 00:05:03,041
[gasps]

74
00:05:04,125 --> 00:05:06,791
[SERVICE MAN 5A] I guess
we can do that this time.

75
00:05:09,291 --> 00:05:10,916
[SAKURA]
By the way,

76
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,875
thank you very much
for coming to my aid.

77
00:05:12,958 --> 00:05:16,041
[KIKYO] No problem. It was the
least I could do to atone!

78
00:05:16,125 --> 00:05:18,375
But, listen, Sakura.
We're the same age.

79
00:05:18,458 --> 00:05:20,500
You don't have to speak
to us so formally.

80
00:05:20,583 --> 00:05:22,208
I'd like to think we're friends!

81
00:05:22,291 --> 00:05:24,375
Yes, you've been acting
like we're your elders.

82
00:05:24,458 --> 00:05:27,083
[gasps] Um. Yeah.

83
00:05:27,166 --> 00:05:28,875
Makes sense.

84
00:05:28,958 --> 00:05:30,041
I will try.

85
00:05:30,125 --> 00:05:31,583
I mean, I'll do my best.

86
00:05:31,666 --> 00:05:33,625
No need to force
anything, either!

87
00:05:33,708 --> 00:05:35,208
[SAKURA]
Um. Right, I won't.

88
00:05:35,291 --> 00:05:37,208
[KIKYO]
Mm-hm!

89
00:05:37,291 --> 00:05:38,875
I'll be back in a bit.

90
00:05:38,958 --> 00:05:40,625
I'm gonna go freshen up.

91
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,875
[AYANOKOJI]
Being alone with her is awkward.

92
00:05:49,958 --> 00:05:50,750
[gasps]

93
00:05:50,833 --> 00:05:51,833
[AYANOKOJI]
Hm?

94
00:05:54,958 --> 00:05:56,458
Is something on your mind?

95
00:05:56,541 --> 00:05:57,750
Do you not feel
comfortable with the--?

96
00:05:57,833 --> 00:06:01,041
Listen. What do you
think I should do?

97
00:06:01,125 --> 00:06:04,666
I can't figure out what
would be best for everyone.

98
00:06:04,750 --> 00:06:07,041
Oh, you mean about Sudo?

99
00:06:07,125 --> 00:06:09,416
The best thing would be
to do what you want.

100
00:06:09,500 --> 00:06:11,416
[gasps] "Do what I want"?

101
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:12,916
That's right.

102
00:06:14,333 --> 00:06:15,916
[SAKURA]
If I keep quiet,

103
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:18,166
I know I'm going to regret it.

104
00:06:18,250 --> 00:06:20,666
[AYANOKOJI] Why are you talking
to me about this?

105
00:06:20,750 --> 00:06:24,041
Your eyes. There's
nothing scary in them.

106
00:06:24,125 --> 00:06:25,625
Eyes?

107
00:06:25,708 --> 00:06:26,791
Never mind.

108
00:06:26,875 --> 00:06:28,958
It's... hard to...

109
00:06:29,041 --> 00:06:30,500
If you need some advice,

110
00:06:30,583 --> 00:06:33,125
I think Kushida's more versed
in this kind of stuff.

111
00:06:33,208 --> 00:06:35,375
She showed up for you today.

112
00:06:37,541 --> 00:06:39,791
[AYANOKOJI]
That's interesting.

113
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:44,833
[AYANOKOJI]
I can tell that she's grateful,

114
00:06:44,916 --> 00:06:47,541
but she doesn't seem
to fully trust Kushida.

115
00:06:47,625 --> 00:06:50,375
Maybe she's more
perceptive than most.

116
00:06:51,541 --> 00:06:55,166
You said you'd regret it if you
kept silent about the fight.

117
00:06:55,250 --> 00:06:56,875
Yeah.

118
00:06:56,958 --> 00:06:59,833
Well, I think you already
know what to do.

119
00:06:59,916 --> 00:07:01,166
[gasps]

120
00:07:01,250 --> 00:07:02,916
[AYANOKOJI]
Don't do it for Sudo,

121
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:05,750
or Kushida, or for any
of our classmates.

122
00:07:05,833 --> 00:07:07,875
Push all of those thoughts
out of your mind.

123
00:07:07,958 --> 00:07:09,125
They don't serve you.

124
00:07:09,208 --> 00:07:11,041
[SAKURA] Serve me?
What do you mean by that?

125
00:07:11,125 --> 00:07:13,083
[AYANOKOJI] Thinking that way
will only convolute things

126
00:07:13,166 --> 00:07:15,083
and make the choice
more difficult.

127
00:07:15,166 --> 00:07:19,083
You should trust your instincts,
and testify for your sake alone.

128
00:07:19,166 --> 00:07:22,666
You mean do the right
thing... for me?

129
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:24,583
That's motivation enough.

130
00:07:24,666 --> 00:07:25,958
[gasps]

131
00:07:28,125 --> 00:07:30,458
[KIKYO] Sorry for taking
so long in there!

132
00:07:30,541 --> 00:07:31,916
Oh. Welcome back.

133
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,250
All right. Do you guys think

134
00:07:33,333 --> 00:07:34,875
that we should call
it a day now?

135
00:07:34,958 --> 00:07:36,333
It is getting pretty late.

136
00:07:36,416 --> 00:07:38,958
You're right. Hey,
would you mind terribly

137
00:07:39,041 --> 00:07:41,500
if I swung by your room
a little later tonight?

138
00:07:41,583 --> 00:07:42,833
Huh?

139
00:07:44,958 --> 00:07:46,791
[KIKYO]
Thanks for having me!

140
00:07:50,083 --> 00:07:52,000
You just had to come to my room?

141
00:07:52,083 --> 00:07:52,833
What's this about?

142
00:07:52,916 --> 00:07:54,083
I found some stuff online

143
00:07:54,166 --> 00:07:57,000
that I thought you might
be interested to see.

144
00:07:57,083 --> 00:07:59,541
Does this girl look
familiar to you?

145
00:08:04,625 --> 00:08:07,666
[AYANOKOJI]
Hold on. Is that Sakura?

146
00:08:07,750 --> 00:08:09,125
It's hard to say if it's her.

147
00:08:09,208 --> 00:08:11,291
I can't tell just from
the pictures alone.

148
00:08:11,375 --> 00:08:13,875
But this one was definitely
taken in one of the dorms here.

149
00:08:13,958 --> 00:08:15,666
[KIKYO]
Do you think it's her, then?

150
00:08:15,750 --> 00:08:17,250
Well, it could be.

151
00:08:17,333 --> 00:08:19,375
I thought it was strange that
she was wearing fake glasses,

152
00:08:19,458 --> 00:08:21,125
but now it makes perfect sense.

153
00:08:21,208 --> 00:08:22,541
[KIKYO]
They're fake?

154
00:08:22,625 --> 00:08:25,708
[AYANOKOJI] There was no
distortion behind the lenses.

155
00:08:25,791 --> 00:08:28,375
So you think she's wearing
them to disguise her face?

156
00:08:28,458 --> 00:08:30,500
Could that be why she
didn't want to testify?

157
00:08:30,583 --> 00:08:32,750
[phone chimes]

158
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:34,458
[KIKYO]
It's a message from Sakura.

159
00:08:34,541 --> 00:08:36,291
Let's see here...

160
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,375
You're not gonna believe this.

161
00:08:38,458 --> 00:08:40,708
She might be willing
to help us defend Sudo!

162
00:08:40,791 --> 00:08:43,791
[AYANOKOJI] I guess going
with her today was worth it.

163
00:08:43,875 --> 00:08:48,291
I'm glad she decided she could
trust us, but I wonder why.

164
00:08:50,375 --> 00:08:52,208
[KIKYO]
Hey.

165
00:08:52,291 --> 00:08:54,291
Ayanokoji, are you sure
you're not trying

166
00:08:54,375 --> 00:08:57,750
to hide anything
from me? For real.

167
00:09:06,041 --> 00:09:07,750
[AKANEAKENE]
I've sent out the notification.

168
00:09:07,833 --> 00:09:09,666
All in classes C
and D were invited.

169
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:13,083
The arbitration hearing is
set to take place tomorrow.

170
00:09:14,166 --> 00:09:16,041
Is that so?

171
00:09:17,541 --> 00:09:19,708
[MANABU]
Class D.

172
00:09:19,791 --> 00:09:21,833
Uh?

173
00:09:21,916 --> 00:09:23,166
What's wrong?

174
00:09:23,250 --> 00:09:25,833
Did you spend your entire
day off with Kushida?

175
00:09:25,916 --> 00:09:28,250
Yeah, because of
the thing with Sakura.

176
00:09:28,333 --> 00:09:30,583
Though we couldn't get her
to commit to testifying.

177
00:09:30,666 --> 00:09:32,375
Not definitively.

178
00:09:32,458 --> 00:09:33,541
I see.

179
00:09:33,625 --> 00:09:34,875
[AYANOKOJI]
What's the matter with you?

180
00:09:34,958 --> 00:09:36,791
What do you mean,
"What's the matter?"

181
00:09:36,875 --> 00:09:38,375
[AYANOKOJI]
Well... You are epitomizing

182
00:09:38,458 --> 00:09:39,875
"that-face" at the moment.

183
00:09:39,958 --> 00:09:42,833
Really? And what do
you mean by "that face"?

184
00:09:42,916 --> 00:09:44,333
This is just my face.

185
00:09:44,416 --> 00:09:45,875
Although...

186
00:09:45,958 --> 00:09:48,458
I am amazed at how self-serving
you've been acting recently.

187
00:09:48,541 --> 00:09:50,416
You hesitate when I
ask for a favor,

188
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:53,375
but when Kushida does,
you gladly jump for her.

189
00:09:53,458 --> 00:09:55,583
I'm analyzing, rationally,
and precisely,

190
00:09:55,666 --> 00:09:58,000
what factors
account for the disparity.

191
00:10:01,250 --> 00:10:02,333
Doesn't matter.

192
00:10:02,416 --> 00:10:03,750
Could've fooled me.

193
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:06,083
More importantly.
The student council has

194
00:10:06,166 --> 00:10:09,125
decided on the time of
Sudo's arbitration hearing.

195
00:10:09,208 --> 00:10:10,833
[AYANOKOJI]
When is it?

196
00:10:10,916 --> 00:10:12,958
It's today, after school.

197
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,125
[AKANE] We will now begin
the deliberation proceedings

198
00:10:17,208 --> 00:10:20,208
regarding the violent incident
that occurred last Tuesday.

199
00:10:20,291 --> 00:10:22,750
Your presence is appreciated.

200
00:10:22,833 --> 00:10:24,083
Now, first of all,

201
00:10:24,166 --> 00:10:27,250
I will preside today, as
Student Council Secretary.

202
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:28,791
The student council president,

203
00:10:28,875 --> 00:10:31,708
attending arbitration over a
little brawl such as this one?

204
00:10:31,791 --> 00:10:33,708
I never dreamed I
would see this day.

205
00:10:33,791 --> 00:10:36,166
[MANABU] My extremely busy
schedule often prevents me from

206
00:10:36,250 --> 00:10:39,625
being present at proceedings
I would prefer to join.

207
00:10:39,708 --> 00:10:41,500
As a rule, though,
I try to attend.

208
00:10:41,583 --> 00:10:43,833
Oh, of course. A coincidence.

209
00:10:43,916 --> 00:10:45,291
[MANABU]
Indeed...

210
00:10:47,625 --> 00:10:49,125
[AYANOKOJI]
Horikita wasn't expecting

211
00:10:49,208 --> 00:10:50,791
her brother to be here.

212
00:10:50,875 --> 00:10:54,958
It seems like his presence
might throw off her game.

213
00:10:55,041 --> 00:10:58,625
Let's begin. The object here
is to ascertain the truth.

214
00:10:58,708 --> 00:11:01,416
Which version of
the events is factual.

215
00:11:01,500 --> 00:11:02,833
Is that acceptable, sir?

216
00:11:02,916 --> 00:11:05,416
[MANABU]
Yes, you may proceed.

217
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:08,666
[AKANE] Komiya et al, you allege
that Sudo summoned you to

218
00:11:08,750 --> 00:11:11,458
the special annex last Tuesday,
where he then attacked you.

219
00:11:11,541 --> 00:11:13,041
Sudo denies your claim.

220
00:11:13,125 --> 00:11:16,291
He insists that Komiya
summoned him to the annex.

221
00:11:16,375 --> 00:11:18,958
Your versions of these
events are contradictory.

222
00:11:19,041 --> 00:11:21,333
We can be certain
of only one thing.

223
00:11:21,416 --> 00:11:23,416
Sudo attacked
and injured you three.

224
00:11:23,500 --> 00:11:26,875
Komiya, Kondo, and Ishizaki
are the victims here,

225
00:11:26,958 --> 00:11:28,625
and we will proceed
under the agreement

226
00:11:28,708 --> 00:11:30,500
that they are the plaintiffs.

227
00:11:30,583 --> 00:11:33,125
Sudo's the defendant
in this case.

228
00:11:33,208 --> 00:11:35,291
[KEN growls]
I'll admit that I beat them up!

229
00:11:35,375 --> 00:11:37,625
But these jerks are
the real attackers!

230
00:11:37,708 --> 00:11:39,416
[AYANOKOJI] Putting the
focus on their injuries

231
00:11:39,500 --> 00:11:40,916
and giving Sudo free reign here

232
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:43,541
will do nothing but
harm our case.

233
00:11:43,625 --> 00:11:45,208
Horikita.

234
00:11:45,291 --> 00:11:46,500
[KEN]
...you're jealous that I got

235
00:11:46,583 --> 00:11:47,833
bumped up to first string!

236
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:49,875
You always try to sabotage
me at practice, but it--

237
00:11:49,958 --> 00:11:52,041
[AKANE] Silence, please.
Return to your seat.

238
00:11:52,125 --> 00:11:54,125
Without any new evidence
or testimony,

239
00:11:54,208 --> 00:11:56,416
we will proceed under the
aforementioned assumptions.

240
00:11:56,500 --> 00:11:58,375
Is this acceptable?

241
00:12:06,208 --> 00:12:07,208
[MANABU]
It's quite apparent

242
00:12:07,291 --> 00:12:09,291
there was no need
for adjudication.

243
00:12:09,375 --> 00:12:12,125
Judging by the severity of
the plaintiffs' conditions,

244
00:12:12,208 --> 00:12:14,833
it's clear that the violence
was one-sided.

245
00:12:14,916 --> 00:12:16,750
I believe this is
sufficient evidence

246
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:18,708
to allow me to make my decision.

