00:12:21,416 --> 00:12:23,833
due to Sudo's absence of
injuries. And the plaintiffs'...

249
00:12:23,916 --> 00:12:26,833
[gasps]

250
00:12:26,916 --> 00:12:31,208
[gasping] Hey! Stop it!

251
00:12:31,291 --> 00:12:32,541
[KEN]
Uh...

252
00:12:32,625 --> 00:12:35,125
[gasping continues]

253
00:12:35,208 --> 00:12:37,208
[SUZUNE sputtering]
Cut it out.

254
00:12:37,291 --> 00:12:39,000
[AYANOKOJI]
When someone's spacing out,

255
00:12:39,083 --> 00:12:42,208
a strong physical stimulus can
often snap them out of it.

256
00:12:42,291 --> 00:12:45,333
The stakes are too high
for me to do nothing.

257
00:12:45,416 --> 00:12:47,208
[SUZUNE]
...come on!  Uh!

258
00:12:52,666 --> 00:12:56,208
If you don't start fighting now,
we're going to lose this case.

259
00:12:56,291 --> 00:12:57,416
[gasps]

260
00:13:00,958 --> 00:13:02,708
[SUZUNE]
I beg your pardon.

261
00:13:02,791 --> 00:13:06,125
Before we break, I would like
to question the witnesses.

262
00:13:06,208 --> 00:13:08,083
Would that be acceptable?

263
00:13:08,166 --> 00:13:09,375
President?

264
00:13:09,458 --> 00:13:10,500
I will allow it.

265
00:13:10,583 --> 00:13:13,625
[inhales, exhales]

266
00:13:13,708 --> 00:13:15,166
The first question.

267
00:13:15,250 --> 00:13:18,375
What were the circumstances
under which Sudo summoned you?

268
00:13:18,458 --> 00:13:20,625
I need an answer.

269
00:13:20,708 --> 00:13:22,333
Uh, when practice was over,

270
00:13:22,416 --> 00:13:24,208
he just said he wanted
to talk to me.

271
00:13:24,291 --> 00:13:25,708
[SUZUNE]
I see.

272
00:13:25,791 --> 00:13:27,916
And what was your reasoning for
bringing Ishizaki with you

273
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,333
to the special annex?

274
00:13:29,416 --> 00:13:31,750
He's not on the basketball
team, as far as I know.

275
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:33,791
There was no reason
for him to be present.

276
00:13:33,875 --> 00:13:36,500
I brought him 'cause I
wanted extra protection.

277
00:13:36,583 --> 00:13:38,000
Protection?

278
00:13:38,083 --> 00:13:41,041
Everyone in school knows what
a violent guy Sudo can be.

279
00:13:41,125 --> 00:13:42,666
And he's pretty big, too!

280
00:13:42,750 --> 00:13:43,875
[SUZUNE]
So you're saying you thought

281
00:13:43,958 --> 00:13:45,625
he might attack you, right?

282
00:13:45,708 --> 00:13:46,916
[KOMIYA]
That's right!

283
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:49,416
[AYANOKOJI] That sounds
like a studied response.

284
00:13:49,500 --> 00:13:52,250
If I understand, you claim
you brought Ishizaki

285
00:13:52,333 --> 00:13:55,708
as a bodyguard, because of
his reputation as a fighter?

286
00:13:55,791 --> 00:13:58,041
Yeah, I did it to
protect myself!

287
00:13:58,125 --> 00:13:59,541
Understood.

288
00:13:59,625 --> 00:14:02,000
I have some knowledge of martial
arts, as a matter of fact.

289
00:14:02,083 --> 00:14:04,000
Sudo faced multiple adversaries

290
00:14:04,083 --> 00:14:06,916
which is exponentially
more difficult to do.

291
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:08,750
For him to beat you so soundly,

292
00:14:08,833 --> 00:14:10,583
especially with
Ishizaki at your back

293
00:14:10,666 --> 00:14:12,500
defending you,
doesn't quite add up.

294
00:14:12,583 --> 00:14:14,458
Uh! It does!

295
00:14:14,541 --> 00:14:17,083
He only beat us because we
didn't want to get into a fight!

296
00:14:17,166 --> 00:14:18,375
[SUZUNE]
If you didn't want a fight,

297
00:14:18,458 --> 00:14:20,541
why would you go, knowing
Sudo's propensities?

298
00:14:20,625 --> 00:14:22,125
And if you weren't
fighting back,

299
00:14:22,208 --> 00:14:24,583
how would all three of you end
up with such severe injuries?

300
00:14:24,666 --> 00:14:27,208
Common sense tells me
Horikita has a good point.

301
00:14:27,291 --> 00:14:29,375
[KOMIYA] You can't use common
sense with Sudo!

302
00:14:29,458 --> 00:14:31,208
He doesn't operate that way!

303
00:14:31,291 --> 00:14:33,291
He's a violent,
unpredictable psychopath!

304
00:14:33,375 --> 00:14:34,541
Well, you're in luck,

305
00:14:34,625 --> 00:14:36,458
because someone witnessed
the entire fight.

306
00:14:36,541 --> 00:14:37,291
[SAKAGAMI gasps]

307
00:14:37,375 --> 00:14:38,458
[KEN gasps]

308
00:14:42,916 --> 00:14:45,333
Would the witness
please step forward?

309
00:14:50,833 --> 00:14:51,916
[AKANE]
Welcome, Miss.

310
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:54,458
Would you state your name,
for the record?

311
00:14:54,541 --> 00:14:57,625
Yes. Airi Sakura.

312
00:14:57,708 --> 00:14:59,541
I'm from Class One-D.

313
00:14:59,625 --> 00:15:02,250
[AKANE]
Please take a seat, Miss Sakura.

314
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:03,708
[SAKURA]
Okay...

315
00:15:08,750 --> 00:15:09,875
Sakura.

316
00:15:09,958 --> 00:15:11,875
[gasps]

317
00:15:11,958 --> 00:15:14,875
I did see it. I witnessed
the whole thing.

318
00:15:14,958 --> 00:15:17,208
Sudo has been telling
the truth this whole time.

319
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:20,125
The Class C students attacked
him first, like he said.

320
00:15:20,208 --> 00:15:22,666
I'm sure of it. They're lying.

321
00:15:22,750 --> 00:15:25,000
Your name's Sakura, is it not?

322
00:15:25,083 --> 00:15:28,166
If you did see the fight, then
why didn't you come forward

323
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:29,750
with your knowledge
before this point?

324
00:15:29,833 --> 00:15:32,291
Well, you see... Because...

325
00:15:32,375 --> 00:15:37,041
[sighs] Honestly, Class D
students are all the same.

326
00:15:37,125 --> 00:15:39,166
I promise this is the truth.

327
00:15:39,250 --> 00:15:40,875
I'm not lying, I swear.

328
00:15:40,958 --> 00:15:44,416
Oh, Sakura. Miss Airi Sakura.

329
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:45,833
Let's be honest now.

330
00:15:45,916 --> 00:15:47,875
Are you sure they
haven't coerced you?

331
00:15:47,958 --> 00:15:51,041
The stakes are high, and they'd
do anything to save Sudo.

332
00:15:51,125 --> 00:15:52,125
[gasps]

333
00:15:52,208 --> 00:15:53,625
[AYANOKOJI]
This could go badly.

334
00:15:53,708 --> 00:15:55,208
Spin it how you wish.

335
00:15:55,291 --> 00:15:57,375
The fact that she's here proves
that she witnessed the fight.

336
00:15:57,458 --> 00:15:59,083
I mean, think about it.

337
00:15:59,166 --> 00:16:01,208
If she hadn't, why would
she show up today,

338
00:16:01,291 --> 00:16:03,333
even if we tried to coerce her?

339
00:16:03,416 --> 00:16:04,666
Oh?

340
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:06,833
If all we needed was
someone who'd lie,

341
00:16:06,916 --> 00:16:09,833
why would we choose a girl like
Sakura, who hates to speak up?

342
00:16:09,916 --> 00:16:12,500
Perhaps to lend an air of
credibility to your case,

343
00:16:12,583 --> 00:16:15,083
you specifically chose
someone who is well-behaved.

344
00:16:15,166 --> 00:16:16,625
That's all you've got?

345
00:16:16,708 --> 00:16:18,666
You're the ones with
the burden of proof,

346
00:16:18,750 --> 00:16:20,041
and from where I
sit, the facts--

347
00:16:20,125 --> 00:16:22,458
It's immoral of you to
take advantage of this girl.

348
00:16:22,541 --> 00:16:24,916
She's weak-willed,
so you manipulate her.

349
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,750
That is not what's going on!

350
00:16:26,833 --> 00:16:29,166
Just look at how hard
she's trembling over there!

351
00:16:29,250 --> 00:16:30,583
You put such a burden on her.

352
00:16:30,666 --> 00:16:33,041
I have real proof!

353
00:16:33,125 --> 00:16:36,333
I saw the fight. I'll prove it.

354
00:16:36,416 --> 00:16:38,666
You are only digging
yourselves a deeper hole.

355
00:16:38,750 --> 00:16:40,125
[SAKURA]
Here it is.

356
00:16:40,208 --> 00:16:43,541
The proof that I was there.
In the annex last Tuesday.

357
00:16:43,625 --> 00:16:45,375
See for yourself.

358
00:16:45,958 --> 00:16:47,500
[gasps]

359
00:16:47,583 --> 00:16:48,500
Let's see it.

360
00:16:48,583 --> 00:16:49,833
Yes.

361
00:16:56,583 --> 00:16:58,125
[SAKURA]
I was there that afternoon,

362
00:16:58,208 --> 00:17:00,000
looking for a place
to take pictures.

363
00:17:00,083 --> 00:17:01,541
I don't like to take
them around people,

364
00:17:01,625 --> 00:17:03,208
and I knew the annex
would be empty.

365
00:17:03,291 --> 00:17:05,125
The photo is dated, too.

366
00:17:05,208 --> 00:17:08,041
Dates on digital photos are
relatively simple to alter,

367
00:17:08,125 --> 00:17:10,916
Miss Sakura. Your proof
is rather insubstantial.

368
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:13,041
Just a minute, Mr. Sakagami.

369
00:17:13,125 --> 00:17:15,666
This photo is sufficient
proof after all.

370
00:17:15,750 --> 00:17:17,625
[SAKAGAMI]
Hm? Ah.

371
00:17:22,208 --> 00:17:24,000
Thank you, sir.

372
00:17:24,083 --> 00:17:26,000
I hope this one will
be proof enough.

373
00:17:26,083 --> 00:17:28,166
I told you that I was
telling the truth.

374
00:17:28,250 --> 00:17:30,625
Thank you so much, Sakura.

375
00:17:30,708 --> 00:17:31,875
[gasps]

376
00:17:36,541 --> 00:17:38,041
[SAKAGAMI]
I'll grant you that much.

377
00:17:38,125 --> 00:17:40,000
It seems that you
were indeed present

378
00:17:40,083 --> 00:17:42,416
in the special annex on
the day in question.

379
00:17:42,500 --> 00:17:44,458
But your photo still
does nothing to prove

380
00:17:44,541 --> 00:17:46,291
that Sudo didn't
start the fight.

381
00:17:46,375 --> 00:17:47,791
It also doesn't provide evidence

382
00:17:47,875 --> 00:17:50,041
that you really witnessed
everything that happened.

383
00:17:50,125 --> 00:17:51,791
[SAKURA]
But I did.

384
00:17:51,875 --> 00:17:54,958
So then, I propose a compromise.

385
00:17:55,041 --> 00:17:57,083
A compromise? What kind?

386
00:17:57,166 --> 00:17:58,875
[SAKAGAMI] Despite the
"evidence" you provided,

387
00:17:58,958 --> 00:18:00,750
you still don't have
any definitive proof.

388
00:18:00,833 --> 00:18:03,333
However, it appears that
Class C may indeed

389
00:18:03,416 --> 00:18:06,666
bear some responsibility
in this debacle.

390
00:18:07,916 --> 00:18:10,583
[SAKAGAMI] I recommend a
two-week suspension for Sudo.

391
00:18:10,666 --> 00:18:13,458
And a one-week suspension
for the Class-C students.

392
00:18:13,541 --> 00:18:15,083
Is that acceptable?

393
00:18:15,166 --> 00:18:17,083
The difference in length
is commensurate

394
00:18:17,166 --> 00:18:19,500
to the severity in harm
done to each party.

395
00:18:19,583 --> 00:18:21,541
[growls]

396
00:18:21,625 --> 00:18:24,333
[AYANOKOJI] If Sakura hadn't
come forward with her testimony,

397
00:18:24,416 --> 00:18:27,583
Sudo would have been suspended
for a month, at the very least.

398
00:18:27,666 --> 00:18:30,583
It is a good bargain, actually.

399
00:18:30,666 --> 00:18:34,375
Ms. Chabashira, does that idea
sound satisfactory to you?

400
00:18:34,458 --> 00:18:39,208
It would appear we have reached
an agreement that will suffice.

401
00:18:39,291 --> 00:18:42,583
[AYANOKOJI] Sakura, you did
everything you could.

402
00:18:47,208 --> 00:18:48,750
Then, that's it.

403
00:18:48,833 --> 00:18:51,625
Miss Horikita,
as representative of Class D,

404
00:18:51,708 --> 00:18:55,250
what's your opinion
of the agreement?

405
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:57,250
[SUZUNE]
This is my final word.

406
00:18:57,333 --> 00:18:59,000
Sudo has a problem.

407
00:18:59,083 --> 00:19:01,291
I think he contributed
to this, ultimately.

408
00:19:01,375 --> 00:19:04,125
Even if he's not the one
who threw the first punch.

409
00:19:04,208 --> 00:19:06,375
He has no sense of how
he affects others.

410
00:19:06,458 --> 00:19:09,541
Actions have consequences,
but he doesn't see that.

411
00:19:09,625 --> 00:19:11,333
Incidents like this
will not stop.

412
00:19:11,416 --> 00:19:12,666
[gasps] What?!

413
00:19:12,750 --> 00:19:14,458
You need to see the
truth of the matter.

414
00:19:14,541 --> 00:19:17,916
Your poor attitude is what
started all of this, really.

415
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:20,041
He does need to reflect
on his actions.

416
00:19:20,125 --> 00:19:23,458
But not the missteps you claim
he took in fight last Tuesday.

417
00:19:23,541 --> 00:19:26,083
I mean that he should reevaluate
the person he has been

418
00:19:26,166 --> 00:19:27,791
this whole school year.

419
00:19:27,875 --> 00:19:29,250
Horikita?

420
00:19:29,333 --> 00:19:31,458
In regards to the incident
we're discussing right now,

421
00:19:31,541 --> 00:19:32,958
that's different.

422
00:19:33,041 --> 00:19:36,125
I truly believe Sudo is free
of all guilt in the matter.

423
00:19:40,375 --> 00:19:42,583
The truth is, I know that Sudo

424
00:19:42,666 --> 00:19:44,875
didn't stumble into that
fight of his own accord.

425
00:19:44,958 --> 00:19:47,958
This was a premeditated set-up,
instigated by Class C,

426
00:19:48,041 --> 00:19:50,541
and that is truly heinous.

427
00:19:50,625 --> 00:19:52,375
I will not back down.

428
00:19:52,458 --> 00:19:54,916
I assert that he is innocent.

429
00:19:56,583 --> 00:19:59,583
[laughs] Premeditated set-up?

430
00:19:59,666 --> 00:20:01,708
That's hilarious, young lady.

431
00:20:01,791 --> 00:20:03,041
I think the president's
sister is a--

432
00:20:03,125 --> 00:20:04,916
As the witness
testified earlier,

433
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:07,125
Sudo's not guilty in this.

434
00:20:07,208 --> 00:20:10,041
I implore you to make
the appropriate decision.

435
00:20:10,125 --> 00:20:12,333
We've been victimized
by him! He's guilty!

436
00:20:12,416 --> 00:20:14,291
You shut your mouth! Jerk!

437
00:20:14,375 --> 00:20:16,458
I'm innocent,
and all of you know it!

438
00:20:16,541 --> 00:20:18,000
You're just trying
to sabotage me

439
00:20:18,083 --> 00:20:19,291
and usurp my place
on the team...!

440
00:20:19,375 --> 00:20:20,958
[MANABU]
Just as I predicted.

441
00:20:21,041 --> 00:20:23,291
This hearing was a waste
of everyone's time.

442
00:20:23,375 --> 00:20:26,250
I'm appalled at the pathetic
behavior on display right now.

443
00:20:26,333 --> 00:20:29,333
Nothing can be settled unless
the liars come forward.

444
00:20:29,416 --> 00:20:31,333
[AKANE]
I agree. This is pointless.

445
00:20:31,416 --> 00:20:33,375
[MANABU]
Therefore, I ask you, Class C.

446
00:20:33,458 --> 00:20:35,541
Can you honestly say right
now that the statements

447
00:20:35,625 --> 00:20:38,208
you've made today are
the unadulterated truth?

448
00:20:38,291 --> 00:20:40,250
What? Of course they're true!

449
00:20:40,333 --> 00:20:42,208
[MANABU]
What about Class D?

450
00:20:42,291 --> 00:20:43,041
Certainly.

451
00:20:43,125 --> 00:20:44,500
[MANABU]
Very well, then.

452
00:20:44,583 --> 00:20:46,875
I will announce my decision
tomorrow at four o'clock.

453
00:20:46,958 --> 00:20:48,875
If I receive no
amended statements,

454
00:20:48,958 --> 00:20:50,291
as in admission of guilt,

455
00:20:50,375 --> 00:20:52,875
nor proof of your opponents'
guilt by then,

456
00:20:52,958 --> 00:20:56,875
I will be putting expulsion
on the table as well.

457
00:20:56,958 --> 00:20:58,458
That is all.

458
00:21:01,625 --> 00:21:03,375
[AYANOKOJI]
Do we have a chance?

459
00:21:03,458 --> 00:21:08,625
Well, I don't intend to lose,
and I never give up, either.

460
00:21:08,708 --> 00:21:10,625
I'm sorry.

461
00:21:10,708 --> 00:21:12,125
I should have just spoken up

462
00:21:12,208 --> 00:21:14,875
from the very beginning
about what I saw.

463
00:21:14,958 --> 00:21:18,750
I'm not... I'm not brave.

464
00:21:18,833 --> 00:21:21,041
You did just fine. It's okay.

465
00:21:21,125 --> 00:21:22,916
But it's not!

466
00:21:28,416 --> 00:21:30,708
[MANABU]
Why are you two still here?

467
00:21:30,791 --> 00:21:32,541
When you showed up
with Suzune today,

468
00:21:32,625 --> 00:21:34,250
I assumed you had a strategy.

469
00:21:34,333 --> 00:21:37,291
But, I suppose I grossly
overestimated the both of you.

470
00:21:37,375 --> 00:21:39,791
I never claimed to be
some star detective,

471
00:21:39,875 --> 00:21:42,041
and I'm not a trial
lawyer, either.

472
00:21:42,125 --> 00:21:44,208
So, no, I don't have a strategy.

473
00:21:44,291 --> 00:21:46,375
You mean Suzune went
out on a limb today?

474
00:21:46,458 --> 00:21:48,416
She truly believes
he's innocent?

475
00:21:48,500 --> 00:21:51,000
[AYANOKOJI]
I guess it's a radical idea.

476
00:21:51,083 --> 00:21:53,583
[MANABU]
Interesting.

477
00:21:53,666 --> 00:21:54,916
Your name's Sakura, right?

478
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:57,833
[gasps] Yes.

479
00:21:57,916 --> 00:22:01,250
If you can't provide evidence
to corroborate your claims,

480
00:22:01,333 --> 00:22:02,500
they're nothing but lies,

481
00:22:02,583 --> 00:22:04,708
and your mask will
become your prison.

482
00:22:04,791 --> 00:22:08,000
But... It's not a lie.

483
00:22:08,083 --> 00:22:12,125
I swear.
I was telling the truth.

484
00:22:12,208 --> 00:22:14,083
[AYANOKOJI]
I believe every word.

485
00:22:14,166 --> 00:22:16,166
[SAKURA gasps]

486
00:22:16,250 --> 00:22:19,916
[MANABU]
I see. Well, in that case...

487
00:22:25,833 --> 00:22:27,208
[AKANE gasping]

488
00:22:27,291 --> 00:22:28,833
[SAKURA gasping]

489
00:22:28,916 --> 00:22:31,916
Do you have what it takes
to prove her right?

490
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:34,166
I guess you'll
find out tomorrow.

